POLICE have arrested a man after a woman was sexually assaulted outside a high school in broad daylight.
The victim, who is in her 40s, was walking near Drumchapel High School in Glasgow when the man grabbed her from behind on Monday evening.
After a grapple with the attacker, she managed to escape and summon help at about 5.30pm on the closed off road near Airgold Drive.
Police have now ordered extra patrols in the area and are appealing for more members of the public to come forward with information.
A Glasgow City Council spokesman said: “Police alerted us to a serious incident which took place near the school on Monday, May 11.
We are working with them to reassure the school community.”
Police Scotland said a man had been arrested in connection with the assault.
A spokesman said: “A 32 year-old man has been arrested and is presently detained in police custody in connection with the incident.
A full report will be sent to the Procurator Fiscal.”
